<!DOCTYPE div SYSTEM "../dtd/tei-epidoc.dtd">
<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" id="abbreviationsunderstood">
    <head>Identification and expansion of abbreviations understood by the editor</head>
    <div id="abbreviationsunderstood-typographic" type="gl-typographic">
        <head>Traditional typographic representation</head>
        <list type="ordered">
            <item><bibl><title level="a" type="abbreviated"><xref href="bibliography.xml#panciera">Panciera</xref></title>, 
                <abbr expan="page">p.</abbr><biblScope type="pages">17</biblScope></bibl>: 
                <list type="ordered" lang="lat">
                        <item>co(n)s(ul)</item>
                        <item>Aug(ustus)</item>
                        <item lang="en">Not covered</item>
                        <item lang="en">Not covered</item>
                        <item lang="en">Not covered</item>
                </list></item>
        </list>
    </div>
    <div id="abbreviationsunderstood-encoding" type="gl-encoding">
        <head>EpiDoc encoding</head>
        <list type="ordered">
            <item><tag>expan</tag><tag>abbr</tag>co<tag>/abbr</tag><tag>supplied reason="abbreviation"</tag>n<tag>/supplied</tag><tag>abbr</tag>s<tag>/abbr</tag><tag>supplied reason="abbreviation"</tag>ul<tag>/supplied</tag><tag>/expan</tag></item>
            <item><tag>expan</tag><tag>abbr</tag>Aug<tag>/abbr</tag><tag>supplied reason="abbreviation"</tag>ustus<tag>/supplied</tag><tag>/expan</tag></item>
            <item><tag>expan</tag><tag>abbr</tag>Aug<tag>orig</tag>g<tag>/orig</tag><tag>/abbr</tag><tag>supplied reason="abbreviation"</tag>usti duo<tag>/supplied</tag><tag>/expan</tag></item>
            <item><tag>expan</tag><tag>abbr</tag>pr<tag>orig</tag><tag>mark type="stop/</tag><tag>/orig</tag><tag>/abbr</tag><tag>supplied reason="abbreviation"</tag>esbyter<tag>/supplied</tag><tag>/expan</tag></item>
            <item id="multi-word-example"><tag>expan</tag><tag>abbr</tag>D<tag>/abbr</tag><tag>supplied reason="abbreviation"</tag>is<tag>/supplied</tag><tag>/expan</tag> <tag>expan</tag><tag>abbr</tag>M<tag>/abbr</tag><tag>supplied reason="abbreviation"</tag>anibus<tag>/supplied</tag><tag>/expan</tag></item>
        </list>
        <p>NOTE: Abbreviated phrases (<abbr expan="for example = exempli gratia">e.g.</abbr>,
                <foreign lang="lat">d(is) m(anibus)</foreign>) should be marked-up word-by-word, as
            illustrated in <ref target="multi-word-example">the example above</ref> rather than as a
            whole phrase, like: 
            <list type="unordered">
                <item><hi rend="strong">No:</hi> <tag>expan</tag><tag>abbr</tag>d<tag>/abbr</tag><tag>supplied reason="abbreviation"</tag>is<tag>/supplied</tag>
                    <tag>abbr</tag>m<tag>/abbr</tag><tag>supplied reason="abbreviation"</tag>anibus<tag>/supplied</tag><tag>/expan</tag></item>
                <item><hi rend="strong">No:</hi> <tag>abbr expan="dis manibus"</tag>dm<tag>/abbr</tag> or</item>
            </list> 
            We are using the <tag>abbr</tag> tag to mark abbreviated words, not acronyms or
            otherwise abbreviated phrases. If an application needs to be able to identify and expand
            acronyms and abbreviated phrases, it will need to do so by processing the text to
            aggregate sequences of <tag>abbr</tag>-tagged words. </p>
    </div>
    <div id="abbreviationsunderstood-edition" type="gl-edition" lang="lat">
        <head lang="en">EpiDoc appearance with standard XSLT</head>
        <list type="ordered">
            <item><expan><abbr>co</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">n</supplied><abbr>s</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">ul</supplied></expan></item>
            <item><expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">ustus</supplied></expan></item>
            <item><expan><abbr>Aug<orig>g</orig></abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">usti duo</supplied></expan></item>
            <item><expan><abbr>pr<orig><mark type="stop"/></orig></abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">esbyter</supplied></expan></item>
            <item><expan><abbr>d</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">is</supplied></expan>  <expan><abbr>m</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">anibus</supplied></expan></item>
        </list>
    </div>
